        "created_at": "2024-08-06T19:54:03.520Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I\u2019m going to be uncorking a Jamet C\u00f4te-R\u00f4tie tomorrow for a friend who loves them and rarely gets to drink them. However, here in France I only own some 2018, 2019 and 2020. I haven\u2019t tried any of those vintages yet. Anybody with experience with them and a desire to offer advice?</p>\n<p>Based on <a class=\"mention\" href=\"/u/a_so\">@A_So</a> notes, I was thinking 18.</p>\n<p>I\u2019ll probably also pop a 2014 Clusel-Roch Vialli\u00e8re and a bottle of champagne (either La Cuv\u00e9e des Gentlemen from De Lozey or L\u2019Intemporelle from Mailly).</p>\n<p>Thanks!</p>",
        "post_number": 1,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 9,
