      {
        "id": 4433144,
        "name": "Phil T r o t t i e r",
        "username": "Phil_T_r_o_t_t_e_r",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/phil_t_r_o_t_t_e_r/{size}/215593_2.png",
        "created_at": "2024-08-07T21:03:23.578Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I went with 2018 <img src=\"https://www.wineberserkers.com/images/emoji/unicode/+1.png?v=12\" title=\":+1:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":+1:\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\"></p>\n<aside class=\"quote quote-modified\" data-post=\"4600\" data-topic=\"285895\">\n  <div class=\"title\">\n    <div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n    <img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://www.wineberserkers.com/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/phil_t_r_o_t_t_e_r/48/215593_2.png\" class=\"avatar\">\n    <a href=\"https://www.wineberserkers.com/t/what-bottle-of-wine-did-you-open-today-part-2/285895/4600\">What bottle of wine did you open today? (Part 2)</a> <a class=\"badge-category__wrapper \" href=\"/c/wine-talk/5\"><span data-category-id=\"5\" style=\"--category-badge-color: #BF1E2E; --category-badge-text-color: #FFFFFF;\" data-drop-close=\"true\" class=\"badge-category \" title=\"Tasting notes, vintage discussions, wine regions, auction pricing, discount codes\u2026all kinds of wine talk\"><span class=\"badge-category__name\">WINE TALK</span></span></a>\n  </div>\n  <blockquote>\n    <a class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://www.wineberserkers.com/uploads/db0731/original/4X/d/9/d/d9d92008b5931bdeee5332f0816a862021158af9.jpeg\" data-download-href=\"https://www.wineberserkers.com/uploads/db0731/d9d92008b5931bdeee5332f0816a862021158af9\" title=\"20240807_191346\">[20240807_191346]</a> \nDisclaimer: we sell this. \nOk. \n <a class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://www.wineberserkers.com/uploads/db0731/original/4X/4/b/8/4b8edaaef360a69358a52aeed816e2f3cf4fdffc.jpeg\" data-download-href=\"https://www.wineberserkers.com/uploads/db0731/4b8edaaef360a69358a52aeed816e2f3cf4fdffc\" title=\"20240807_172312\">[20240807_172312]</a> \nThis was fun. \nClusel-Roch La Vialli\u00e8re 2014 \nGreat nose: red berries, violets and lilacs, sweet spices and red meat. This is lively, lots of red berries, great syrah meatiness, salivating acidity amd some grippiness on the tannins. Wonderful to drink now but still some upside. Love this. \nDomaine Jamet C\u00f4te-R\u00f4tie 2018 \nSuper expressive black and blue fruit. The nose also displays smoke, black olives, and dried herbs. It fee\u2026\n  </blockquote>\n</aside>\n",
